result.execSummary:
The defendant Randall W. Andrews was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Amphetamine/LSD/Psilocin, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(d).
  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Pay court costs.   **NOTE: THE DEFENDANT IS ORDERED TO PAY ALL COURT OBLIGATIONS TO THE CLERK OF COURTS OFFICE.   Payment is due within 30 days.  If the Defendant cannot make the payment, he/she must report to the Clerk of Courts Office to set up a payment plan.  Failure to comply will result in other collection methods including a civil Judgment and/or suspension of your drivers license for one (1) year.  This judgment may be collected by income assignment if you fail to pay fines and costs as ordered.
-------------------------------

IT IS HEREBY ORDERED THAT the defendant's excess work release funds be applied to any & all outstanding Court obligations while serving his mandatory jail sentence.
-------------------------------

Defendant to work full time, attend school full time or a combination of the two. 
-------------------------------

No alcohol.   No illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.   Not to operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license.
-------------------------------

IT IS ORDERED, pursuant to Wis. Stats. Sec. 973.015, that upon successful completion of the sentence imposed WITH NO VIOLATION OF THE RULES OF PROBATION, the Clerk of Court shall issue an order expunging the record.
-------------------------------

Counseling as recommended by Probation Agent. Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge.
-------------------------------

AODA assessment and follow through with recommendations.
-------------------------------

8:32 am  Case called.  Appearances given.  Daniel A. Necci appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deft Randall W. Andrews in court with Atty Stephen R Kramer.  
Matter is before the Court for plea and sentencing.  State files AMENDED CRIMINAL COMPLAINT.    
Court has reviewed the terms of the plea agreement and makes parties aware that Court is not inclined to grant expungement.  If the parties wish to argue their positions for special disposition, the Court will hear that but the Court wanted the parties to know up front that it it is not inclined to grant it.  Attorney Kramer understands, appreciates the Court letting them know up front and indicates the deft still wants to go forward.  Atty Kramer would like a brief recess to speak with his client.  8:34 am  Court takes recess to allow Atty Kramer to discuss this further with his client.  8:35 am  Court in session.  Atty Kramer indicates that his client is aware that the Court is not bound by any recommendation of the parties, and he is ready, willing and able to proceed today knowing that.  Mr. Andrews confirms that he does wish to proceed today.  Atty Kramer recites terms of the plea agreement.  8:39 am  Atty Necci confirms the agreement as recited by Atty Necci.  8:39 am  Response by Mr. Andrews to Court's questions.  

8:42 am  Plea questionnaire is filed with Court.  Defendant enters GUILTY pleas to Counts #1, #2 and #3 of Amended Complaint.  Court conducts plea colloquy with Mr. Andrews.  Court gives warning with regard to deportation if not a citizen of the United States.  Court accepts guilty pleas, enters judgment of conviction and will proceed to sentencing.  
8:47 am  Atty Necci indicates the State is jointly making a recommendation for special disposition.    8:48 am  Argument by Atty Kramer.  
8:54 am  Statement by Mr. Andrews.  Response by Mr. Andrews to Court's questions.  
8:58 am  Further comments by Atty Kramer.  8:59 am  Further statement by defendant.  
9:00 am  Court proceeds with sentencing the defendant.  

SENTENCE:  
Imposed and STAYED:
Ct #1 - 9 months jail w/Huber;  Ct #2 - 6 months jail w/Huber CS to Ct #1;  Ct #3 - 30 days jail w/Huber CS to Cts #1 & #2

TWO (2) years probation with conditions:  
1)  On Ct. #1 - 4 months in WCJ with release release; Turn in date:  9/23/2016;  2)  Pay court costs and DOC supervision fees;  3)  AODA assessment and follow through w/rec. counseling;  
4)  Counseling as recommended by Prob. Agent;  5)  No weapons;  6)  No alcohol.  No drugs or drug paraphernalia.  No driving without a valid license;  7)  Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.  8)  Deft to work full time, attend school full time or a combination of the two.  9)  Deft will not request early termination of probation.  10)  Special Disposition pursuant to Sec. 973.015, Wis. Stats. WITH NO VIOLATIONS OF PROBATION.
